## Quiz 3 — Spot the error

Each statement has one mistake. Find it.

1. *"The Metropolis acceptance ratio depends on `p(y)`, the marginal likelihood, which is why it's hard to compute."*
2. *"In the Beta-Binomial model, the posterior mean is `(α₀ + s) / (α₀ + β₀)`."*
3. *"R̂ close to 1 guarantees the chain has converged."*
4. *"The Laplace prior gives the Ridge penalty in MAP estimation."*
5. *"In the conjugate Normal model, the posterior mean of μ is `(κ₀ μ₀ + ȳ) / (κ₀ + n)`."*
6. *"As n → ∞, the posterior mean stays fixed at the prior mean because the prior is informative."*
7. *"A trace plot that drifts upward over 4000 iterations means the proposal step size is too small."*

